Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a method that uses convolutional neural network algorithm to segment GSV images and predict obstructions on sun glare. 
- cs.GR (Graphics): The paper uses GSV panorama images to estimate and predict the occurrence of sun glare. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The proposed method can be used by traffic planners to mitigate the sun glare and decrease the potential traffic accidents caused by the sun glare. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses a machine learning algorithm to predict the presence of sun glare. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a method that uses a convolutional neural network algorithm to segment GSV images and predict obstructions on sun glare.
